## Vector Quantization

### Vector quantization

**矢量量化**( **VQ** ) 是一种来自信号处理的经典量化技术，它允许通过原型矢量的分布对概率密度函数进行建模。它最初用于数据压缩。它的工作原理是将大量点（向量）划分为具有大致相同数量的最接近它们的点的组。每个组都由其质心点表示，如k-means和其他一些聚类算法。

##### Learning an Effective Codebook of Image

learn a convolutional model consisting of an encoder $E$ and a decoder $G$, such that taken together, they learn to represent images with codes from a learned discrete codebook $Z = \{z_k\}^K_{k=1}⊂ R^{n_Z}$.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) 

More precisely, we approximate a given image $x$ by $\hat{x} = G(z_q)$. We obtain $z_q$ using the encoding $\hat{z} = E(x) ∈ \R^{h×w×n_z}$. and a subsequent element-wise quantization $q(·)$ of each spatial code $\hat{z}_{ij} ∈ \R^{n_z}$ onto its closest codebook entry $z_k$: 
$$
\begin{align*}
z_q=&q(\hat{z})\\=&(\text{arg}\min ||z_{ij}-z_k||)\in \R^{h\times w\times n_z}
\end{align*}
$$
The reconstruction $\hat{x}\approx x$ is then given by
$$
\hat{x}=G(z_q)=G(q(E(x)))
$$

##### Latent Transformers

With $E$ and $G$ available, we can now represent images in terms of the codebook-indices of their encodings. 

More precisely, the quantized encoding of an image $x$ is given by $z_q = q(E(x)) ∈ \R^{h×w×n_z}$ and is equivalent to a sequence $s ∈ \{0, . . . , |Z|−1\}^{h\times w}$ of indices from the codebook, which is obtained by replacing each code by its index in the codebook $Z$:
$$
s_{ij} = k \;\;\;\text{such that} (z_q)_{ij} = z_k.
$$
